In one month, the number of cases of coronavirus in the region gradually increased.
These cases were largely linked to the Huaanan Sea fruit market. The market also sold live animals, which led to the theory that the virus came from one of these animals. In other words, it was believed to have a zoonotic origin. On 26 December, a group of patients were observed and treated by Dr. Zhang Jixian at Hubei's Provincial Hospital. On the following day, the doctor informed Wuhan Jianghan's Prevention and Control Center.
On December 30, a group of doctors from Wuhan's Central Hospital warned their colleagues about a SARS-type coronavirus.
