The governor of New York Andrew Cuomo announced that tests with chloroquine and hydroxychloroquine of the state of New York would begin on 24 March. On 28 March, the FDA authorised the use of hydroxychloroquine sulphate and chloroquine phosphate by means of an Emergency Use Authorisation (EUU).
The treatment was not approved by the FDA clinical trial process and is authorised by the EU only as experimental treatment for emergency use in hospitalized patients who cannot receive treatment in a clinical trial.
